    <section class="m-6 p-3 bg-gray-800 rounded-md">
        <h2 class="text-center text-lg font-semibold">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div tabindex="0" class="collapse collapse-arrow rounded-box">
            <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-medium">
                How do I use First Line Response?
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content">
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside">
                    <li>To start, click the red "New Call" button. In the box to the right, you'll see that this created
                        and automatically selected a new call.</li>
                    <li>Some fields, including the date, time, and call ID fields, are autofilled to save time.</li>
                    <li>Type information into the other fields as needed and hit the "enter" key or click "Save Call" to
                        save the call.</li>
                    <li>To add apparatus, just type the apparatus name into the "apparatus" column of the Department
                        Response section. After saving, click the boxes to the right to timestamp each movement.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div tabindex="0" class="collapse collapse-arrow rounded-box">
            <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-medium">
                Is First Line Response avaiable for download?
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content">
                <p>Our team is still working to create a stand alone version using Electron. The current expected
                    release date is tentatively 2023.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div tabindex="0" class="collapse collapse-arrow rounded-box">
            <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-medium">
                What are some upcoming features?
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content">
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
                    <li>Create a stand alone version with a local database.</li>
                    <li>Introduce React.JS for more fluid interactions.</li>
                    <li>Add team support, where multiple users can access the same calls simulataneously.</li>
                    <li>Auto-remove completed calls (calls where all apparatus have returned to quarters).</li>
                    <li>Create a call history button.</li>
                    <li>Options to export call information as a PDF or for print.</li>
                    <li>Start new users with an example call.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

    </section>

